Expert Report on Smart Contract Verification Mechanisms in MetaMask-Compatible Networks
​Introduction: The Nexus of Code, Custody, and Cryptography
​The proliferation of decentralized applications (dApps) across MetaMask-compatible networks, primarily those leveraging the Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM) ecosystem, necessitates robust mechanisms for verifying the integrity and security of deployed smart contracts. Smart contracts are self-executing agreements whose terms are encoded directly into persistent, immutable bytecode.12 The verification process is complex, relying not only on the cryptographic guarantees of the underlying Layer 1 (L1) infrastructure but also on auditing the human and institutional actors involved in deployment and the transparency provided by block explorers. 


